    },
    {
      "id": "BURiE2Pk-xJx1KmZX2Ds4",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 721.0979996593032,
      "y": -5310.770936103479,
      "width": 951.57958984375,
      "height": 420,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1Z",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 689917411,
      "version": 1105,
      "versionNonce": 1401168922,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776034791809,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Fixed outcomes vs branching paths? what are the ways to progress?\nDevelopment path 1: Story driven (coffee talk, val-hall-a)\n    + interesting and engaging\n    - requires in-depth branching design \n    - less gameplay focused (which conflicts with my personal goals)\n    + could be fun\nDevelopment path 2: Shop management driven (papa's pizzeria)\n    + easier to POC\n    + more opportunities for gameplay focused decisions\n    + easier to expand in the future\n    + aligns more with my personal goals\n    - less interesting to play (but that's not really my goal)",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Fixed outcomes vs branching paths? what are the ways to progress?\nDevelopment path 1: Story driven (coffee talk, val-hall-a)\n    + interesting and engaging\n    - requires in-depth branching design \n    - less gameplay focused (which conflicts with my personal goals)\n    + could be fun\nDevelopment path 2: Shop management driven (papa's pizzeria)\n    + easier to POC\n    + more opportunities for gameplay focused decisions\n    + easier to expand in the future\n    + aligns more with my personal goals\n    - less interesting to play (but that's not really my goal)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "nnbZlwIaCiWOkHtOPiXS_",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 3105.693237754541,
      "y": -4734.985221817765,
      "width": 1466.2057291666665,
      "height": 840,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b2B",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1662392739,
      "version": 1547,
      "versionNonce": 150606034,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775524528873,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Each day\n> fixed number of characters visit the shop (pre-determined? random? hybrid?)\n> each character will have specific desired attributes for that day\n> successfully completing encounters with characters builds a relationship score\n> failing encounters will either not impact or will negatively impact their relationship score\n> at the end of the day the player may purchase shop upgrades and useful items\n\nEncounters\n> Customer enters with dialogue. Provides implicit clues about desires, emotional state, and expectations\n> Player uses their deck to construct a fortune. Limited resources (hand size, slots, etc.). Player is\nbalancing building a strong result and aligning with the customer\n> (TBD) Player chooses how to present the reading. Presentation influences how the result is perceived\nbased on how well it aligns with the customer\n> Customer reacts based on how well the reading matched their desires and how it was delivered.\nResults determine relationship change, rewards (currency, items, etc.), possible story progression.\n\nOverarching\n> characters may visit the shop repeatedly over time\n> each character has certain relationship thresholds\n> upon reaching a relationship threshold with a character, additional story details are revealed\n    * can be in-depth or small surface level details depending on design approach\n\nEnd game\n> the game ends when... ???",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Each day\n> fixed number of characters visit the shop (pre-determined? random? hybrid?)\n> each character will have specific desired attributes for that day\n> successfully completing encounters with characters builds a relationship score\n> failing encounters will either not impact or will negatively impact their relationship score\n> at the end of the day the player may purchase shop upgrades and useful items\n\nEncounters\n> Customer enters with dialogue. Provides implicit clues about desires, emotional state, and expectations\n> Player uses their deck to construct a fortune. Limited resources (hand size, slots, etc.). Player is balancing building a strong result and aligning with the customer\n> (TBD) Player chooses how to present the reading. Presentation influences how the result is perceived\nbased on how well it aligns with the customer\n> Customer reacts based on how well the reading matched their desires and how it was delivered.\nResults determine relationship change, rewards (currency, items, etc.), possible story progression.\n\nOverarching\n> characters may visit the shop repeatedly over time\n> each character has certain relationship thresholds\n> upon reaching a relationship threshold with a character, additional story details are revealed\n    * can be in-depth or small surface level details depending on design approach\n\nEnd game\n> the game ends when... ???",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
